ltivation". The contributions can be read as a plea to re-establish a language-critical component (as opposed to a merely descriptive one) in the engagement with (German) language and literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aGerman languagexPhilosophyvCongresses. 0aGerman literaturexHistory and criticismvCongresses. 0aLanguage and languages in literaturevCongresses. 4aAachen ‹1999›. 4aGermanistik. 4aKongress. 4aLiteraturwissenschaft. 4aSprachkritik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aBreuer, Dieter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGellhaus, Axel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGellhaus, Axel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMüller, Richard Matthias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNussbaumer, Markus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSitta, Horst, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSitta, Horst, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC0 cprintz978348431218040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311091999840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110919998423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110919998/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GLCc2000d2014